        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:48PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 948 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Fenton to South Lyon to Dixboro to near
Blissfield. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Conway Township, Auburn Hills, Pleasant Ridge, Scofield,
Wolverine Lake, La Salle, Holloway, Southgate, Munson, Hudson,
Hartland, South Rockwood, Oak Grove, Onsted, Hudson Mills, Wayne,
Milan, Springville, and Britton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
